                    </article>

                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>She also commended Duke President Vincent Price for his statement in response to the most recent swastika found on campus.&nbsp;</p>
<p>“These acts need to be acknowledged and condemned every time,” she said. “When this first began to happen with the flyering, campus administrators would denounce the flyer and say this doesn’t comply with the values of our university—and that was that. They need to be stronger, to say who these folks are, to say that this is anti-Semitism or white supremacy, or whatever it is, and we condemn it and we stand by all students at our university and we are going to do what we can to root this out.”</p>
